#X text 125 63 With [lowpass~] we can easily implement polyphony sonce it handles multichannel connections - as well as the other filters from ELSE like [moog~] and objects in the patch that are all from ELSE (besides [*~]). You can also try [moog~] and it's a matter of taste which one sounds better or not \, as they sound quite different., f 79;
#X obj 485 714 else/gatenorm~;
#X text 393 552 We have independent envelopes for amplitude and filter \, and the filter one still has basically a decay stage. for didactical purposes \, we normalize the gate input with [op~ >] instead of using the built in 'normalization' parameter on the ELSE objects. You can do this if you're using something else..., f 50;
#X text 392 659 This makes it behave consistently even for quiter notes and it's an important detail to consider. There's also a [gatenorm~] abstraction for you to check out., f 50;
